#import "template.typ": *

#let metadata = (
  title: "Practice Flight Test",
  unit: "Group A (3-Axis) | Phase 5 — Lesson 1 | All Elements",
  author: "C.Moroney",
  version: "v1.0.0",
)

#let lesson = (
title: [Practice Flight Test]

,aim: [
Demonstrate all 16 flight elements and weight and balance competency to C standard in a simulated flight test.
]

,overview: [
Lesson 5.2 is the practice flight test. Before this lesson proceeds, a formal pre-flight-test readiness check must be completed and confirmed in writing in the student training record.

The practice test covers all 16 elements of the v8 Group A syllabus integrated into a complete flight, including pre-flight planning with weight and balance, weather, and NOTAMs. The student operates as PIC throughout; the instructor adopts the examiner role — silent assessor, no coaching. Any element assessed as NC identifies a specific target for remediation in L5.3 before the actual flight test is booked.
]

,learning_outcomes: [
No new learning outcomes — this is a comprehensive assessment of all previously taught elements against C standard.
]

,theory_knowledge: [
Consolidation of all Phase 1–5 theory. All theory exams must be confirmed complete before this lesson commences.
]

,ground_brief_topics: [
Total time: 30 minutes \
Equipment required: Student training record, logbook, all exam results, weight and balance worksheet, NAIPS access, POH \

*Pre-Flight-Test Readiness Check — MANDATORY GATE* (15 minutes)

The following must be confirmed and signed off in the student training record before the practice test proceeds. If any item is not confirmed, the practice test is deferred until it is resolved.

_Logbook requirements:_
- ☐ Student pilot logbook is complete and up to date: all flights entered, all columns completed and totalled in pencil, all required instructor signatures present
- ☐ Total flight time confirmed: minimum 20 hours dual flight training
- ☐ Solo PIC time confirmed: minimum 5 hours PIC (including circuit and training area solo time)

_Theory exam requirements:_
- ☐ BAK exam passed: minimum 80%, KDR completed and recorded
- ☐ Air Legislation exam passed: minimum 80%, KDR completed and recorded
- ☐ Human Factors exam passed: minimum 80%, KDR completed and recorded
- ☐ Radio Exam: minimum 80%, KDR completed and recorded
- ☐ Pre-Solo Air Legislation exam: already recorded from Phase 2
- ☐ Weight and Balance assessment (L5.1): C standard confirmed and recorded

_Regulatory requirements:_
- ☐ Valid RAAus Student Pilot Certificate held
- ☐ Financial flying membership of RAAus current
- ☐ Health declaration current (driver licence medical standard)
- ☐ All 16 flight elements recorded at C standard in the student training record

_Flight test booking:_
- ☐ Flight test has been booked with the CFI or a designated examiner (PE) for a specific date
- ☐ Student has been informed of the flight test format, duration, and assessment criteria
- ☐ Student has the RAAus flight test paperwork ready for the actual test date

*Practice Test Brief* (15 minutes)
- Instructor confirms the practice test format: examiner role; no coaching; no prompting
- Student plans the complete flight as PIC: weather, NOTAMs, weight and balance, route, element sequence
- Student briefs the plan to the instructor/examiner
- Weight and balance calculation reviewed: student must demonstrate C standard calculation before flight proceeds
]

,ground_tasks:[
#text(size:12pt)[*Student plans and briefs the complete flight independently:*]
- NAIPS: TAF/GAF obtained and interpreted; conditions assessed; brief presented
- NOTAMs: checked; any relevant items identified
- Weight and balance: calculated for today's actual loading; plotted on envelope; within limits confirmed; brief to instructor
- Maintenance release: reviewed; brief presented
- Route: departure, training area, element sequence (to cover all 16 elements in a logical order), return, circuit and landing
- HASSELL minimum heights
- EFATO plan
- Radio plan and transponder codes

#text(size:12pt)[*Instructor/Examiner*]
- Receives full brief; confirms readiness gate is complete
- Confirms conditions are suitable for all planned elements including stalling
- Provides no content input from this point
- Adopts examiner role for the complete flight
]

,in_flight_tasks:[
#text(size:12pt)[*Complete Practice Flight Test — Student as PIC, Instructor as Examiner*]
The instructor does not coach, prompt, or intervene except for safety. Assessment is recorded per element and per E13 competency variable.

Student conducts a complete flight covering all 16 elements:
- Pre-flight inspection and documentation (E1)
- Startup, taxi, runup, radio calls, transponder (E13)
- Weight and balance confirmed before boarding
- Takeoff and after-takeoff checks (E8)
- Straight and level at cruise and slow cruise (E3)
- Climbing: Vy and Vx (E4)
- Descending: all profiles (E5)
- Basic turning: 15° and 30° AoB (E6)
- Slow flight and stall recognition (E7)
- Advanced turning: 60° AoB, dutch roll, sustained 360° (E9)
- Scenario based stalling: at least two scenarios (E10)
- Forced landing simulation: complete ABCDEF sequence and FLWOP circuit (E14)
- Training area operations: departure, overhead join (E15)
- Unusual attitude recovery: one nose-high, one nose-low (E16)
- Circuit and circuit emergencies: normal circuit, EFATO simulation, flapless (E11)
- Landing: normal powered approach to full-stop (E12)
- Radio and avionics throughout (E13)

#text(size:12pt)[*Examiner Notes*]
- Record C, S (approaching C but not yet fully consistent), or NC for each element
- NC items are priority targets for L5.3 remediation
- If student is clearly not at C standard on multiple elements — stop the flight; debrief; reschedule the practice test after targeted remediation
]

,common_errors:[
- *Element-specific errors*: Refer to common errors in each Phase 1–4 lesson plan for remediation guidance.
- *Weight and balance incomplete or incorrect*: NC for E1 — calculation and briefing are part of the flight preparation requirement.
- *HASSELL omitted before stalling or steep turns*: NC for E9 and E10 — non-negotiable.
- *Stable approach gate not applied*: NC for E12 — the gate must be assessed on every approach.
- *Radio omissions during transitions*: NC for E13 — all required calls must be made.
- *ABCDEF sequence incomplete or out of order*: NC for E14 — sequence must be from memory.
]

,post_flight:[
- *Student Leads Debrief* (10 min): Student self-assesses each element against C standard; identifies any areas not yet at C standard.
- *Examiner Provides Formal Practice Test Result* (20 min):
  - Reports C, approaching C, or NC for each element with specific comments
  - NC items: explains exactly what was observed; agrees specific remediation targets for L5.3
  - Confirms flight test readiness: "Ready to test" or "Remediation required before test"
  - If ready — confirms flight test date is booked; reviews any administrative items outstanding
  - If not ready — agrees the minimum remediation required and expected timeline

- *Flight test booking confirmed*: Date, examiner, and any outstanding administrative items confirmed in writing in the training record.
]

,standards_for_progression:[
*Pre-practice test gate — all must be confirmed before the practice test proceeds:*
- ☐ Logbook complete and up to date; all flights entered and signed
- ☐ Minimum 20 hours dual flight training
- ☐ Minimum 5 hours solo PIC time
- ☐ BAK, Air Legislation, Radio and Human Factors exams passed and recorded
- ☐ Weight and Balance assessment at C standard
- ☐ All 16 flight elements at C standard in training record
- ☐ Flight test booked with CFI or designated examiner

*Practice test result — to advance to flight test without remediation:*
- All 16 elements assessed as C by the examiner
- Weight and balance calculation performed correctly and independently
- No NC items
- Administrative gate confirmed complete

*If NC items exist — L5.3 remediation is required before the flight test proceeds*

- *Outcome*: Practice test result recorded per element in student training record. Flight test readiness confirmed or deferred. Remediation targets specified for any NC items.
]

,safety:[
- *Weather*: All element-specific minima apply: ceiling >3500 ft AGL for stalling, >2500 ft for training area elements, >1500 ft AGL for circuit elements; smooth air preferred; wind \<25 knots
- *Altitude*: HASSELL minimum heights enforced; examiner monitors throughout
- *Emergency Procedures*: EFATO brief before departure; ABCDEF sequence for training area forced landing simulation briefed before flight
- *TEM*:
  - Practice test environment can increase student stress — brief stress management before the flight
  - Examiner must maintain safety readiness throughout; non-interventionist but not passive
  - If student becomes significantly stressed or unsafe — end the practice test; debrief professionally; do not proceed to the actual flight test until readiness is demonstrated
  - Ensure the practice test does not create time pressure that leads to rushed decisions or omitted checks
]

,homework:[
- Review any NC items identified in the practice test debrief; consolidate the specific competency variables that did not meet C standard
- Confirm flight test booking details: date, time, examiner, location, expected duration
- Confirm all administrative requirements are complete: logbook signed, theory exams recorded, RAAus membership current
- Reflect:
  - "Which element in the practice test felt least automatic? What specific practice would address that?"
  - "If you could do one more flight before the test, what would you focus on?"
]
)

#show: body => lesson_plan(metadata, lesson, body)